CLASSICS cercars

Here are authentic wines of a previous period—treasures that have survived the wine merchants’ need to sell and the wine lover’s impulse to open the cork. Everyone of these has started as a great wine and has been permitted to reach its full maturation in bottle. Commercially they are non-existent and their acquisition is not far removed from the art collector’s search for a rare painting.

Tasting any of these wines can provide an aesthetic experience for the sensitive

palate quite in the same league as listening to a good concert or watching a

Shakespearean play well performed.
